  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e01\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455240704/hB485B960\" id=\"_r_a_10455240704\" width=\"800\" height=\"420\" alt=\"Cheezburger Image 10455240704\" title=\"\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003csub\u003eThe image does not depict the actual subjects of the story. Subjects are models.\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis student already completed all of his school credits, and despite one more AP course, had a ton of free periods and “study halls.” Therefore, he decided to attend his real class but felt no need to go to study hall, as he had next to no work to complete. This led to the school administration having a vendetta against him for missing class, and so the saga began.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e02\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455231488/h06ACCFFD/back-late-90s-imagine-school-systems-work-much-different-at-hs-level-now-and-my-kids-arent-old-yet\" id=\"_r_a_10455231488\" width=\"800\" height=\"329\" alt=\"For reference this took place back in the late 90\u0026#39;s. I\u0026#39;d imagine school systems work much different at the HS level now, and my kids aren\u0026#39;t that old. yet.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e03\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455232256/hB1B7AD81/arts-and-taught-too-so-got-an-extra-gym-credit-early-changed-my-mind-because-wanted-graduate\" id=\"_r_a_10455232256\" width=\"800\" height=\"392\" alt=\"Okay so it was my senior year of HS and I had had just enough credits in my Junior year to graduate. I had taken martial arts and taught it too so I got an extra gym credit early, I changed my mind because I wanted to graduate\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e04\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455232768/hEB2A7393/physiology-and-some-random-stuff-aps-were-lot-work-and-had-good-test-scores-last-year-already-and\" id=\"_r_a_10455232768\" width=\"800\" height=\"485\" alt=\"with my friends. So I just loaded up my schedule that year with whatever I wanted or I thought would look good to colleges. A few AP courses like US GOV, Physics, Anatomy \u0026amp; Physiology and some random stuff. The AP\u0026#39;S were a lot of work and, I had good test scores from last year already and I\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e05\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455232000/h1B8CB1F5/jewelery-2-class-so-had-3-open-periods-day-surrounding-lunch-magical-and-still-had-1-ap-class-so\" id=\"_r_a_10455232000\" width=\"800\" height=\"364\" alt=\"wasn\u0026#39;t looking to get lower scores on classes I didn\u0026#39;t care about so I dropped Physics/Gov and a random Jewelery 2 class. So I had 3 open periods a day surrounding lunch. It was magical, and i still had 1 AP class so I\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e06\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455231744/h6C9D7EF6/my-parents-worked-so-didnt-know-anything-amiss-till-realized-had-broken-answering-machine-again-90s\" id=\"_r_a_10455231744\" width=\"800\" height=\"318\" alt=\"though I wasn\u0026#39;t messing around too much. Both my parents worked so we didn\u0026#39;t know anything was amiss. Till we realized we had a broken answering machine...again it was the 90\u0026#39;s.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e07\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455232512/h0400B41F/assigned-after-dropped-few-classes-this-hadnt-happened-other-years-as-would-just-be-free-period\" id=\"_r_a_10455232512\" width=\"800\" height=\"459\" alt=\"Apparently my school was calling 3x a day every day to tell us I wasn\u0026#39;t showing up to some study hall class I had been assigned to after I dropped the few classes. This hadn\u0026#39;t happened other years as It would just be a free period.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e08\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455233536/h413BE48A/or-anything-sent-home-this-is-also-around-time-my-mom-starting-her-retirement-being-hair-stylist\" id=\"_r_a_10455233536\" width=\"800\" height=\"495\" alt=\"The funny part was the woman calling us was kind of a b I about it. After the first few days the messages started to get nasty...yet no one said word one to me in the school, or was anything sent home. This is also around the time my mom was starting her retirement from being a hair stylist,\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e09\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455233280/h89242875/are-good-technically-he-could-have-graduated-already-college-aps-are-already-out-so-no-biggie\" id=\"_r_a_10455233280\" width=\"800\" height=\"378\" alt=\"so she\u0026#39;d do like a week on and a week off, and now she was getting the calls. So she tells the woman, shes okay with it, his grades are good, technically he could have graduated already, college. aps are already out, so no biggie.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e10\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455233792/h5AFC5BB3/on-about-irresponsible-all-were-and-she-personally-going-tank-my-applications-could-be-so-brazen\" id=\"_r_a_10455233792\" width=\"800\" height=\"374\" alt=\"Oh that was apparently the wrong thing to say to this lady cause she read my mom the riot act. Going on about how irresponsible we all were and how she was personally going to tank my applications, how could I be so brazen,\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e11\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455234304/h7633CA1D/class-despite-my-parents-approval-repeated-calls-school-and-eventually-they-showed-up-face-face\" id=\"_r_a_10455234304\" width=\"800\" height=\"380\" alt=\"etc etc etc etc crazy level of over reaction. Plus she wouldn\u0026#39;t stop calling for every single class despite my parents approval, repeated calls to the school, and eventually they showed up face to face.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThankfully, the kid\u0026#39;s mom understood the ridiculousness of this situation and was not going to put up with it or let her son\u0026#39;s future be compromised in any way. Cue malicious compliance!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e12\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455234048/hF840277A/accept-their-word-over-phone-or-even-face-face-allowed-leave-as-had-previous-years-w-0-issues-they\" id=\"_r_a_10455234048\" width=\"800\" height=\"383\" alt=\"It was by law they had to report un- pre-approved truancy. So my mom sat down on it, they wouldn\u0026#39;t accept their word over the phone or even face to face that I was allowed to leave (as I had previous years w/ 0 issues...) they\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e13\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455234560/hD2366A5A/knew-they-were-being-detrimental-my-learning-were-essentially-bad-parents-etc-etc-etc-crazy-stuff\" id=\"_r_a_10455234560\" width=\"800\" height=\"507\" alt=\"wanted something in writing. I don\u0026#39;t think any of it was legal or necessary because the lady was telling my parents they had to put all kinds of stuff like they knew they were being detrimental to my learning...were essentially bad parents etc etc etc...crazy stuff.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e14\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10455235584/hAC0D9B30/have-notify-parents-so-she-started-playing-dumb-making-this-lady-call-her-up-every-single-period\" id=\"_r_a_10455235584\" width=\"800\" height=\"436\" alt=\"So my mom gets an idea. She says 100% they aren\u0026#39;t writing anything like that, she looks it up and it is a law that if a student has an unexcused absence they have to notify the parents. So she started 